      right: ["Severe intractable neuropathic pain (NRS 8-10) unresponsive to pharmacotherapy","Progressive motor weakness with sensory loss suggesting evolving radiculopathy or myelopathy","New-onset bowel or bladder dysfunction (cauda equina syndrome -- surgical emergency)","Severe allodynia preventing functional activity, sleep, or ADL performance","TCA toxicity: QT prolongation, cardiac arrhythmia, seizures, anticholinergic crisis","Suicidal ideation in patient on anticonvulsant or antidepressant therapy"]
