        correct: 1,
        rationale: "With a high-probability Wells score (greater than 6), D-dimer is NOT useful (high false negative rate in high pretest probability). The next best step is to start anticoagulation (heparin) and confirm with CT pulmonary angiography. Treatment should not be delayed for confirmation in high-probability cases."
